  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the well-being of persons with disabilities in camp and camp-like settings</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving camp coordination and camp management assistance to vulnerable internally displaced persons. This IOM project, in consultation with organisations of persons with disabilities, seeks to improve the well-being of persons with disabilities, increase their participation and acceptance within their community, and provide a safe physical environment. This project refers persons with disabilities to medical and psychosocial specialists for appropriate treatment, management and counseling; procures assistive devices; and mainstreams inclusion in camp management services. The project provides life-saving assistance to 10,000 people, including 2,500 women, 1,900 men, 5,600 children, and 900 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
